07:18.764 --> 07:20.966
I worked at this school.

07:20.966 --> 07:22.836
Then last spring they fired me,

07:22.836 --> 07:24.704
so I started hitting the bottle.

07:24.704 --> 07:26.005
Hard.

07:26.005 --> 07:28.507
So one night, I'm leaving the bar,

07:28.507 --> 07:30.709
I mean, piss-drunk.

07:30.709 --> 07:34.180
I step out into the street, and then Wham!

07:34.180 --> 07:36.582
starts playing on this guy's car radio,

07:36.582 --> 07:38.518
so I just start dancing around,

07:38.518 --> 07:40.220
you know, it's Wham!

07:40.220 --> 07:41.555
And then bam!

07:41.555 --> 07:43.023
- I got hit by a truck.
- Damn.

07:43.023 --> 07:44.925
I'm telling you, Pac,
I was the best janitor

07:44.925 --> 07:46.927
this school had ever seen.

07:46.927 --> 07:48.228
So what'd you do wrong?

07:48.228 --> 07:49.795
That's just it!

07:49.795 --> 07:51.163
I didn't do anything.

07:51.163 --> 07:52.132
You don't mean...

07:52.132 --> 07:53.867
I was set up.

07:53.867 --> 07:55.534
Something's going on at this school,

07:55.534 --> 07:57.603
something big.

07:57.603 --> 07:59.639
That's why I need you
to clean the one thing

07:59.639 --> 08:01.908
I never could.

08:01.908 --> 08:03.009
My record.

08:03.009 --> 08:05.911
♪

08:07.244 --> 08:08.612
My God!

08:08.612 --> 08:12.612
What does it all mean?

08:13.350 --> 08:14.584
Seriously?

08:14.584 --> 08:16.185
Again?

08:16.185 --> 08:19.221
All right, that is Teddy Biddick.

08:19.221 --> 08:20.624
He's a fourth grader.

08:20.713 --> 08:21.880
A rotten apple, but he knows

08:21.880 --> 08:23.016
how to work the system.

08:23.016 --> 08:24.283
Now how do you roam the halls

08:24.283 --> 08:25.651
without a hall pass?

08:25.651 --> 08:27.954
Easy. You own the halls.

08:27.954 --> 08:30.956
♪

08:30.956 --> 08:32.558
Last year he became hall monitor

08:32.558 --> 08:34.594
courtesy of Principal Herring.

08:34.594 --> 08:36.363
He's been lording it over us ever since.

08:36.363 --> 08:38.398
Let's just say he's a real piece of shit.

08:38.398 --> 08:40.933
Now, Teddy slipped and
fell and broke his arm

08:40.933 --> 08:43.269
supposedly in a puddle
that wasn't even there.

08:43.269 --> 08:44.671
How do I know it wasn't even there?

08:44.671 --> 08:46.405
Because I mopped it up!

08:46.405 --> 08:47.774
I'm sure of it!

08:47.774 --> 08:49.609
- So you took the fall...
- For Teddy's fall.

08:49.609 --> 08:50.876
Let me guess, last fall?

08:50.876 --> 08:53.379
No, last spring. Stay with me here.

08:53.379 --> 08:54.980
There's no way that that kid

08:54.980 --> 08:56.682
slipped in that puddle.

08:56.682 --> 08:58.817
- Unless... he faked it!
- You're mistaken.

08:58.817 --> 09:01.388
Yeah, he faked it.

09:01.388 --> 09:02.721
Start with Teddy,

09:02.721 --> 09:03.990
find out what he knows.

09:03.990 --> 09:05.357
And Pac?

09:05.357 --> 09:07.626
Trust no one.

09:07.626 --> 09:09.328
Not even you?

09:10.897 --> 09:11.998
No, you can trust me.

09:11.998 --> 09:13.399
Well, how can I trust you,

09:13.399 --> 09:16.870
if I can't even trust... myself?

09:16.870 --> 09:18.971
Let's just start at the
beginning again, okay?

09:18.971 --> 09:21.441
You can trust me, and
you can trust yourself.

09:21.441 --> 09:22.942
But no one else. You got it?

09:22.942 --> 09:24.476
Yes, got it. Okay, good.

09:24.476 --> 09:25.979
One last question,

09:25.979 --> 09:29.014
what's the deal with the math problems?

09:29.014 --> 09:31.618
Because something doesn't add up.

09:31.618 --> 09:35.618
♪

09:36.759 --> 09:38.528
Isn't this place amazing?

09:38.528 --> 09:40.397
Millie, what are we doing here?

09:40.397 --> 09:44.768
Sue, have you ever tried possession?

09:44.768 --> 09:46.735
Possession? Is that like a real thing?

09:46.735 --> 09:48.871
Seriously? Oh my God!

09:48.871 --> 09:50.340
You're adorable.

09:50.340 --> 09:51.540
Okay, so check it out.

09:51.540 --> 09:52.942
A ghost can possess a solid

09:52.942 --> 09:54.677
if they're in, like, a really weak state.

09:54.677 --> 09:57.580
Like, say, this gentleman right here.

09:57.580 --> 10:00.517
Fuck you, McAvoy!

10:00.517 --> 10:02.085
So when you possess someone,

10:02.085 --> 10:04.320
you can, like, control them?

10:04.320 --> 10:05.855
Yeah.

10:05.855 --> 10:07.690
I mean, until the host
realizes what's happening

10:07.690 --> 10:09.658
and kicks you out, but usually that takes

10:09.658 --> 10:11.927
long enough that you can get drunk

10:11.927 --> 10:13.596
or take a bath,

10:13.596 --> 10:16.533
or take a bath while getting drunk!

10:16.533 --> 10:19.668
You know, all the best
parts of being a human.

10:19.668 --> 10:21.804
- I don't know.
- Sue!

10:21.804 --> 10:23.673
Live a little.

10:24.573 --> 10:28.573
♪

10:34.017 --> 10:35.051
Bingo.

10:35.051 --> 10:38.587
♪

10:38.587 --> 10:40.456
You Teddy Biddick?

10:40.456 --> 10:42.558
Who the hell wants to know?

10:42.558 --> 10:45.495
♪

10:45.495 --> 10:46.729
Heard you took a pretty nasty fall

10:46.729 --> 10:47.831
last spring there, bud.

10:47.831 --> 10:49.032
Yeah, what about it?

10:49.032 --> 10:50.633
Rumor has it you faked the fall.

10:50.633 --> 10:52.000
Now why would I fake a fall?

10:52.000 --> 10:53.536
Oh, I don't know, a few weeks off

10:53.536 --> 10:54.671
at the end of the school year

10:54.671 --> 10:55.938
doesn't sound so bad.

10:55.938 --> 10:58.006
As much daytime TV and as many Zebra Cakes

10:58.006 --> 10:59.475
as a kid could ever dream of

10:59.475 --> 11:01.477
sounds like a pretty sweet gig to me.

11:01.477 --> 11:02.778
Listen, fatty.

11:02.778 --> 11:04.013
I'm no faker.

11:04.013 --> 11:06.014
Who you calling fatty, short stack?

11:06.014 --> 11:07.115
You're nothing but...

11:07.115 --> 11:11.115
♪

11:11.386 --> 11:12.489
What you looking at?

11:12.489 --> 11:13.923
What?

11:13.923 --> 11:15.557
Nothing.

11:15.557 --> 11:18.495
All right, fine, you didn't fake the fall.

11:18.495 --> 11:19.761
Then why don't you have a cast,

11:19.761 --> 11:20.864
you little rug rat?

11:20.864 --> 11:21.865
Hey, I got it taken off

11:21.865 --> 11:23.899
like three months ago.

11:23.899 --> 11:25.735
How do you think broken bones work, anyway?

11:25.735 --> 11:28.638
I don't know. You tell me.

11:28.638 --> 11:31.073
Seriously, I don't know. You tell me?

11:31.073 --> 11:33.042
Anyway, how would you even fake a fall?

11:34.576 --> 11:36.379
Allow me to demonstrate.

11:36.379 --> 11:37.846
How about the old one, two,

11:37.846 --> 11:39.849
I'm walking over here... yoink!

11:39.849 --> 11:40.984
Oh!

11:40.984 --> 11:41.918
Oh, God.

11:43.452 --> 11:45.522
You know what, Sue? This has been great.

11:45.522 --> 11:46.855
It's nice to have someone listen

11:46.855 --> 11:51.059
to me for a change.

11:51.059 --> 11:52.828
Exactly, right?

11:52.828 --> 11:54.764
Just like that.

11:54.764 --> 11:56.865
Just like that.

11:56.865 --> 11:58.301
I mean, I don't know why I'm so closed off

11:58.301 --> 12:00.336
in the first place.

12:00.336 --> 12:01.738
I mean, my mother...

12:01.738 --> 12:04.440
Ow, ow, ow, ow, ow!

12:04.440 --> 12:05.607
All right, be straight with me.

12:05.607 --> 12:07.043
Is it broken?

12:07.043 --> 12:08.878
How do you think broken bones work?

12:08.878 --> 12:09.979
I don't know.

12:09.979 --> 12:12.548
No one will tell me.

12:12.548 --> 12:14.750
Say, can I have one of those lollipops?

12:14.750 --> 12:16.619
Sorry, students only.

12:16.619 --> 12:17.620
Especially at the rate I'm giving

12:17.620 --> 12:18.988
these things out.

12:18.988 --> 12:20.322
You'd be surprised how many skinned knees

12:20.322 --> 12:21.658
I see at this school.

12:21.658 --> 12:22.991
You got any records of those accidents?

12:22.991 --> 12:24.826
You mean an injury report?

12:24.826 --> 12:26.796
- Yeah.
- Sure.

12:28.063 --> 12:29.599
Attagirl.

12:30.899 --> 12:32.601
♪

12:32.601 --> 12:34.003
Where are you?

12:34.003 --> 12:36.438
Where are you, you
delicious sons of bitches?

12:36.438 --> 12:37.472
Ah, where is it?

12:37.472 --> 12:38.908
Ah!

12:38.908 --> 12:40.442
Bingo.

12:40.442 --> 12:44.313
♪

12:46.915 --> 12:47.783
Here we are.

12:47.783 --> 12:50.419
Thanking you.

12:53.022 --> 12:56.926
♪

12:58.327 --> 12:59.629
Let me know when you're finished.

12:59.629 --> 13:01.697
You got it, doll.

13:01.697 --> 13:02.565
Incident.

13:02.565 --> 13:03.600
Slipped and Fell

13:03.600 --> 13:04.866
Location.

13:04.866 --> 13:07.035
Outside Ms. Fatale Classroom

13:07.035 --> 13:08.937
Oh my God.

13:08.937 --> 13:10.405
This is...

13:10.405 --> 13:12.107
probably, maybe something.

13:12.107 --> 13:13.942
♪

13:13.942 --> 13:15.745
Relax, Sue. It's just possession.

13:15.745 --> 13:17.679
It's not a big deal. Watch!

13:22.585 --> 13:23.653
Hey.

13:23.653 --> 13:25.654
Go on, Sue, jump in!

13:26.822 --> 13:28.024
Come on, Sue.

13:28.024 --> 13:29.024
It's just possession,

13:29.024 --> 13:30.426
everyone's doing it.

13:30.426 --> 13:31.793
Come on.

13:31.793 --> 13:33.462
Go!

13:36.032 --> 13:37.866
Woah!

13:37.866 --> 13:40.636
This is...

13:40.636 --> 13:43.038
crazy.

13:43.038 --> 13:45.341
Feel this! Feel this!

13:45.341 --> 13:46.775
Feel this!

13:46.775 --> 13:48.110
Oh!

13:50.712 --> 13:54.712
♪

14:04.494 --> 14:06.461
Mr. Pacalioglu.

14:06.461 --> 14:09.532
What, uh, what are you doing here?

14:09.532 --> 14:10.966
Are you okay, Ms. Fatale?

14:11.032 --> 14:13.634
I'm... I'm fine! What can I do for you?

14:13.634 --> 14:15.470
Well, I was thumbing
through the school reports;

14:15.470 --> 14:17.038
I was hoping maybe we
could have a jaw wagger.

14:17.107 --> 14:18.109
Okay, I'll talk.

14:18.109 --> 14:19.911
But not here.

14:19.911 --> 14:23.648
Meet me outside in ten minutes.

14:23.648 --> 14:27.118
Well, that seemed a little suspicious.

14:28.152 --> 14:29.553
Hello.

14:29.553 --> 14:32.056
- Uh-oh.
- We just wanna talk.

14:32.056 --> 14:34.792
Run, Pac, Run!

14:34.792 --> 14:37.094
♪

14:42.070 --> 14:43.904
Oh, you did it, Pac.

14:43.904 --> 14:46.341
You're the fastest man alive.

14:46.341 --> 14:47.508
♪

14:47.508 --> 14:48.976
My God.

14:48.976 --> 14:50.411
They're machines!

14:50.411 --> 14:54.349
♪

14:54.349 --> 14:57.150
No running!

14:57.150 --> 15:01.150
♪

15:17.605 --> 15:20.140
Eat that shit!

15:22.409 --> 15:26.047
Ohhh, how I've missed this.

15:27.705 --> 15:30.374
Here. Here. Eat this shit.

15:30.374 --> 15:31.475
Where'd that come from?

15:31.475 --> 15:33.443
Duh. His pocket.

15:33.443 --> 15:35.011
Millie, gross!

15:35.011 --> 15:38.482
Come on, when was the last time you tasted?

15:42.552 --> 15:44.221
Oh my God.

15:44.221 --> 15:45.722
This is so good!

15:45.722 --> 15:47.557
Yeah!

15:47.633 --> 15:50.570
Wait, wait, you got some schmutz.

15:50.570 --> 15:51.504
Slut.

15:56.908 --> 16:00.908
♪

16:06.783 --> 16:09.386
Hey! You're sweating all over the mops.

16:09.386 --> 16:12.255
Dude, what the hell
have you gotten me into?

16:12.426 --> 16:13.394
Look at this!

16:13.394 --> 16:14.695
These are injury reports.

16:14.695 --> 16:15.962
Teddy's not the only one that fell.

16:15.962 --> 16:16.831
There have been a bunch of accidents

16:16.831 --> 16:17.865
over the past few years.

16:17.865 --> 16:19.365
And look, look, look!

16:19.365 --> 16:20.900
All right outside Ms. Fatale's classroom!

16:20.900 --> 16:24.437
And they all happened just before summer.

16:24.437 --> 16:25.806
Of course.

16:25.806 --> 16:27.674
Statewide exams!

16:27.674 --> 16:29.009
♪

16:30.677 --> 16:32.846
You thought she'd get
away with it, didn't ya?

16:32.846 --> 16:34.782
- Excuse me?
- Teddy, 'cuff him!

16:34.782 --> 16:35.816
I don't have handcuffs!

16:35.816 --> 16:37.150
You son of a bitch!

16:37.150 --> 16:38.652
It was all an elaborate ruse,

16:38.652 --> 16:41.788
a set up, a, a...

16:41.788 --> 16:42.755
Web of lies.

16:42.755 --> 16:43.890
A web of flies!

16:43.890 --> 16:45.525
- Thank you.
- Who are you talking to?

16:45.525 --> 16:47.461
You know damn well who I'm talking to.

16:47.461 --> 16:49.028
The old janitor you fired last spring

16:49.028 --> 16:50.364
right before you blamed him

16:50.364 --> 16:51.365
for Teddy's accident.

16:51.365 --> 16:52.533
What? This is absurd!

16:52.533 --> 16:53.933
Oh, is it? Every year kids slip

16:53.933 --> 16:55.568
and fall outside Ms. Fatale's classroom

16:55.568 --> 16:57.337
right before the year-end statewide exams.

16:57.337 --> 16:58.538
Oh sure, a bunch of kids

16:58.538 --> 16:59.673
slipping and breaking their arms

16:59.673 --> 17:00.640
seems innocent enough, right?

17:00.640 --> 17:01.975
Wrong!

17:01.975 --> 17:03.777
Ms. Fatale teaches remedial math,

17:03.777 --> 17:06.145
which I just learned
means math for dumb kids.

17:06.145 --> 17:07.914
So when the dumb kids like Teddy here...

17:07.914 --> 17:09.450
- Hey!
- ... Hurt themselves,

17:09.450 --> 17:10.951
they can't take the exams.

17:10.951 --> 17:13.953
Which means the school
test score averages go...

17:13.953 --> 17:15.454
- Up.
- Up! Yeah!

17:15.454 --> 17:16.723
See, which means the school's doing

17:16.723 --> 17:18.459
a good job, see, which means you get

17:18.459 --> 17:19.826
more cash from the state, see,

17:19.826 --> 17:21.627
which means more fancy new things like that

17:21.627 --> 17:22.962
vending machine outside that I hucked

17:22.962 --> 17:24.865
on the ground and broke
into a million pieces.

17:24.865 --> 17:26.467
It was the perfect crime.

17:26.537 --> 17:27.871
All you needed was a goat to scape,

17:27.871 --> 17:29.807
and who better than this weird old janitor.

17:29.807 --> 17:31.607
- Hey!
- Admit it, Principal Herring!

17:31.607 --> 17:33.609
It was you all along, your goose is cooked.

17:33.609 --> 17:35.078
Teddy, 'cuff him, damn it!

17:35.078 --> 17:36.447
Why would I have handcuffs?

17:36.447 --> 17:37.748
I'm a child!

17:37.748 --> 17:39.083
Are you saying

17:39.083 --> 17:41.617
that the ghost was the janitor?

17:41.617 --> 17:43.519
Yeah, that's what I'm saying, ya dunce!

17:43.519 --> 17:45.622
Well, that makes sense.

17:45.622 --> 17:46.757
Uh.

17:48.659 --> 17:50.527
Watch this!

17:52.695 --> 17:54.832
Hello!

18:00.703 --> 18:01.904
- Oh!
- Ow!

18:01.904 --> 18:04.942
- I can see my bone!
- So as you can see, it was summer,

18:04.942 --> 18:07.411
Ms. Fatale wore skimpy clothing,

18:07.411 --> 18:09.579
and the janitor got distracted.

18:09.579 --> 18:11.548
Case closed.

18:11.548 --> 18:12.915
Well, how do... how do you explain

18:12.915 --> 18:14.852
all the victims being dumb kids?

18:14.852 --> 18:16.519
Because they're the dumb kids.

18:16.519 --> 18:17.855
They don't look where they're going.

18:17.855 --> 18:19.556
- Yeah, that's true.
- Not now, Teddy.

18:19.556 --> 18:22.459
There's no conspiracy, Mr. Pacalioglu.

18:22.459 --> 18:24.694
That janitor, rest his soul,

18:24.694 --> 18:27.998
was just terrible at his job.

18:27.998 --> 18:30.933
Oh my God.

18:30.933 --> 18:33.103
I am a shitty janitor.

18:33.103 --> 18:35.538
♪

18:35.538 --> 18:37.740
I guess I'll just go.

18:37.740 --> 18:42.179
♪

18:42.179 --> 18:45.816
Well, the ghost is gone, so...

18:45.816 --> 18:46.983
you're welcome.

18:46.983 --> 18:48.719
And we should discuss payment.

18:48.719 --> 18:50.820
Well, we'll just deduct your payment

18:50.820 --> 18:52.522
from what you owe us

18:52.522 --> 18:54.424
for the broken vending machine,

18:54.424 --> 18:57.627
which was a gift, by the way.

18:57.627 --> 19:01.432
You owe us a thousand dollars.

19:01.432 --> 19:02.633
Should we just call it even?

19:02.633 --> 19:04.000
♪

19:04.000 --> 19:05.836
Mr. Pacalioglu?

19:05.836 --> 19:09.839
♪

19:09.839 --> 19:11.541
What did you want to talk to me about?

19:11.541 --> 19:12.976
Never mind. I figured that out.

19:12.976 --> 19:14.877
But the one thing that's
still rattling around

19:14.877 --> 19:16.946
in this old jalopy is why
you wanted to talk to me

19:16.946 --> 19:18.648
outside instead of up in your classroom.

19:18.648 --> 19:20.017
Oh, it was quiet hour.

19:20.017 --> 19:21.484
My kids were reading.

19:21.484 --> 19:23.554
Then why were you so nervous?

19:23.554 --> 19:25.923
The book I gave them was off curriculum.

19:25.923 --> 19:27.090
Right.

19:27.090 --> 19:28.424
Well, turns out the ghost

19:28.424 --> 19:29.393
in the back of your classroom

19:29.393 --> 19:30.794
was the old janitor.

19:30.794 --> 19:32.028
He's gone now. He took a hike.

19:32.028 --> 19:32.996
Will?

19:32.996 --> 19:35.065
- Mhm.
- Aw, that's sad.

19:35.065 --> 19:37.101
- I always liked him.
- Yup.

19:37.101 --> 19:38.501
Terrible janitor,

19:38.501 --> 19:40.037
but he always found little ways

19:40.037 --> 19:41.038
to brighten my day.

19:41.038 --> 19:42.673
Hm.

19:42.673 --> 19:44.674
Adiós, amiga.

19:49.512 --> 19:51.949
How 'bout that?

19:51.949 --> 19:54.651
She knew who I was.

19:54.651 --> 19:56.153
You were solving those math problems

19:56.153 --> 19:59.623
to impress the skirt, weren't ya?

19:59.623 --> 20:01.491
I don't know what you're talking about.

20:01.491 --> 20:05.491
♪

20:10.666 --> 20:13.936
- Woah!
- You're a hard man to reach, Pacalioglu.

20:13.936 --> 20:15.105
What do you guys want?

20:15.105 --> 20:16.906
Barry Weinbergerstein sent us.

20:16.906 --> 20:18.174
Sorry about the chase.

20:18.174 --> 20:19.809
We tried calling you, but they said

20:19.809 --> 20:21.444
you were out of minutes.

20:21.444 --> 20:22.880
When you were on Midtown Manhattan Medium,

20:22.880 --> 20:24.448
you tested through the roof.

20:24.448 --> 20:25.414
And we can see why.

20:25.414 --> 20:26.616
That vending machine stunt

20:26.616 --> 20:28.085
you pulled earlier was hilarious!

20:28.085 --> 20:29.452
Hilarious!

20:29.452 --> 20:30.686
What is that? What are you...

20:30.686 --> 20:31.788
What are you guys saying to me?

20:31.788 --> 20:33.022
Mr. Pacalioglu,

20:33.022 --> 20:35.192
Alt TV would like to offer you...

20:35.192 --> 20:38.095
your very own TV show.

20:38.095 --> 20:40.063
- What?
- So what do you say?

20:40.063 --> 20:41.097
You want to make a ton of money

20:41.097 --> 20:42.732
doing virtually nothing?

20:42.732 --> 20:46.936
♪

20:46.936 --> 20:49.573
♪ Oh, yeah ♪

20:54.039 --> 20:54.874
Hey, Sue!

20:54.874 --> 20:55.875
Hey!

20:55.875 --> 20:57.609
- Hi.
- Hey, Kevin.

20:57.609 --> 20:59.111
I didn't think you'd be home until later.

20:59.111 --> 21:00.479
No, no. I'm here now.

21:00.479 --> 21:01.681
I just went and bought this TV

21:01.681 --> 21:03.215
with all the cash that I have.

21:03.215 --> 21:04.817
I certainly did not buy it on credit,

21:04.817 --> 21:06.685
that's not what happened.

21:06.685 --> 21:08.954
So uh, how was hanging
out with Roofie all day?

21:08.954 --> 21:11.057
Uh, it was...

21:11.057 --> 21:12.124
Pac!

21:12.124 --> 21:16.124
Dude, your girlfriend...

21:17.230 --> 21:18.864
was amazing.

21:18.864 --> 21:19.932
Right?

21:19.932 --> 21:21.166
We talked all afternoon,

21:21.166 --> 21:22.867
I got so much stuff off my chest.

21:22.867 --> 21:25.971
Pac, I'm out the drug game.

21:27.772 --> 21:29.174
I'm out!

21:29.174 --> 21:30.776
What did you do?

21:30.776 --> 21:34.776
♪

